(Corrects spelling of name in headline.)  American Express Co. (AXP) , the biggest
U.S. credit-card lender by customer purchases, named  McKesson
Corp. (MCK) ’s Jeffrey C. Campbell as chief financial officer.  Campbell, 52, succeeds Dan Henry, 64, whose retirement was
announced previously, New York-based AmEx said today in
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
